      <div class="apn-r-week">
        <div class="apn-r-week__header">WEEK FOUR</div>
        <div class="apn-r-week__title">Review HRV Data and Optimize Load</div>
        <div class="apn-r-week__focus">FOCUS: DATA REVIEW AND PROTOCOL LOCK</div>

        <p class="apn-r-body">You have 3 weeks of recovery data. Week 4 is about reading it accurately and making decisions that hold for the next 30 days. The protocol does not end at Day 30. It becomes permanent infrastructure for anyone who is serious about sustained performance.</p>

        <ul class="apn-r-action-list">
          <li><strong>Pull your HRV data from all 3 weeks.</strong> Calculate your 7-day rolling average for each week. Is it trending up, flat, or down? Trending up means your training load is appropriate and your recovery protocol is working. Flat with good subjective performance is also acceptable. Trending down despite the protocol indicates training volume may be exceeding your recovery capacity. If your 3-week trend is downward, reduce weekly training volume by 20% before adding any other variables.</li>
          <li><strong>Compare Week 4 soreness to Week 1 soreness.</strong> Your DOMS duration should have reduced measurably. If you scored it on a 1 to 10 scale as assigned in Week 1, you have real data. A reduction of 2 to 3 points in soreness score or a reduction of 12 to 24 hours in soreness duration are the benchmarks for protocol success. If you did not track it, start this week and use it as your new baseline for the next 30 days.</li>
          <li><strong>Adjust training load based on HRV trend.</strong> If your HRV is consistently above your Week 1 baseline, your recovery capacity has increased. You can handle more volume or more intensity. Add it gradually: 10% volume increase maximum per week. If HRV is at or below Week 1, hold current load and give the protocol another 2 weeks before reassessing. Do not increase load on a suppressed recovery trend.</li>
          <li><strong>Lock the three permanent infrastructure habits.</strong> These do not stop at Day 30: protein timing within 45 minutes of every training session, active recovery on rest days, and daily HRV tracking. Everything else in this protocol is enhancing these three. Do not let these three drift.</li>
