          <p class="apn-r-body" style="margin:0;">Full data review: HRV trend, CRP if you measured it, soreness scores, and performance data from your training logs. At your level, the relationship between recovery quality and performance quality should be directly visible in the numbers. If HRV has trended up and performance metrics have improved, you have closed the gap. Maintain the protocol as permanent architecture. Do not rotate off it chasing novelty.</p>
